tedwards@eng.umd.edu (Thomas Grant Edwards) writes:

>I would definately recommend that _anyone_ who owns a cell phone
>get access to a 900 MHz scanner (oh, yeah, you might have to cut
>a few diodes...)

>Cell phones are _not_ secure...be very careful what you say on them!

The US Supreme Court has held that police may freely tape cell-phone
conversations without a warrant. The user has no reasonable
expectation of privacy, the test for when a warrant is required. The
case concerned the admissiblity of a tape of a lawyer talking to his
client.
